Place rack in upper third of oven and preheat to 400 degrees F. In a food processor with the shredding disk or with a hand grater, grate potatoes and onion. Place in a colander and drain well, squeezing out excess moisture. In a large bowl, whisk eggs, salt, 6 tablespoons melted margarine, and flour. Stir in potatoes until well combined. Place remaining melted margarine in a 9x13-inch baking dish. Tilt dish to coat evenly. Pour potato mixture into dish and spread evenly. Bake uncovered for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 375 degrees F and continue baking for 45 minutes more or until top is crisp. Cut into squares.